00:00:40.079 --> 00:00:42.069
nuts in the streets, and the

00:00:42.079 --> 00:00:43.990
Eiffel Tower is on fire. And I said, 'I

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:46.470
don't know how you burn metal, because the

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:48.630
Eiffel Tower is metal.'But I saw it

00:00:48.640 --> 00:00:50.150
burning.

00:00:50.160 --> 00:00:54.069
And so we see over the weekend

00:00:54.079 --> 00:00:57.830
people acting crazy in France and

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:59.990
burning the Eiffel Tower, just like the

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.029
Lord showed us. Was it last

00:01:03.039 --> 00:01:03.750
year?

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:04.869
Yeah, two years ago.

00:01:04.879 --> 00:01:07.510
Two years ago. It's been a while. But I

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:10.950
saw the Eiffel Tower burning, and I said,

00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:12.230
'I don't know what causes the Eiffel

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:14.230
Tower to burn.'And I still don't

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:15.510
understand how that could

00:01:15.510 --> 00:01:15.520
burn—it's

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:18.230
metal. But I guess it's on the bottom.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:21.109
Maybe they lit some tires on fire or

00:01:21.119 --> 00:01:23.749
something. But there it is, just like

00:01:23.759 --> 00:01:26.870
the vision. I saw it burning. Yeah.

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:28.710
It's on the side of it, isn't it, honey?

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:29.350
Yeah.

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:31.429
So, it's not the Eiffel Tower itself;

00:01:31.439 --> 00:01:32.710
it's metal. I was thinking, because

00:01:32.720 --> 00:01:33.990
that's in the vision, I thought, 'How in

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.310
the world does a metal structure

00:01:36.310 --> 00:01:36.320
